                            video Susanna Reid admitted she felt ‘physically sick’ after learning President Vladimir Putin had put Russia’s nuclear forces on high alert amid the Ukraine invasion. Mr Putin’s military continued to advance towards the Ukraine capital of Kyiv over the weekend, but the situation escalated on Sunday when the president ordered his defence minister and army chief to ‘transfer the deterrence forces of the Russian army to a special mode of combat duty’, according to the state-owned TASS news agency. There was no direct mention of atomic weapons but the Russian term for ‘deterrence’ is widely seen as a euphemism for the country’s vast nuclear capabilities. Reacting to the news, Susanna said on Monday’s Good Morning Britain: ‘I think we can all agree, there was a moment yesterday when I felt physically sick.’ For the latest updates on the Russia-Ukraine war, visit our live blog:  Russia-Ukraine live As they broadcasted a clip of Mr Putin relaying the order to his team, Susanna remarked: ‘Look, they’re almost fearful of him.’ Her co-host Adil Ray revealed he had texted Susanna upon hearing about the shocking development, and added: ‘I think it’s the point he would even say that and knowing the fear it would bring to people, and that is pretty vile.’ {"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"VideoObject","name":"Metro.co.uk","duration":"T51S","thumbnailUrl":"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/02/27/14/54716095-0-image-a-7_1645970605728.jpg","uploadDate":"2022-02-27T14:03:14+0000","description":"Vladimir Putin has ordered Russian nuclear deterrent forces on alert amid tensions with the West over Ukraine.","contentUrl":"https://videos.metro.co.uk/video/met/2022/02/27/3227509917867655755/640x360_MP4_3227509917867655755.mp4","height":360,"width":640}  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web
